Subject: Offer of Stipend-Based Internship — AI Intern

Dear [INTERN_NAME],

We are pleased to offer you a stipend-based internship with Omninuera for the role of AI Intern. This letter sets out the key terms and conditions of the internship. Please read the document carefully and sign and return a copy to indicate your acceptance.

1. Position and Reporting
- Position: AI Intern.
- Supervisor: [SUPERVISOR_NAME], [SUPERVISOR_TITLE].
- Reporting: You will report to [SUPERVISOR_NAME] (or their designate) for the duration of the internship.

2. Offer Type and Nature of Relationship
- This is a stipend-based internship and not full-time employment. The internship is intended for training/educational/short-term project purposes and does not by itself create an employment relationship beyond the stipend specified below.
- Explicitly, this offer provides a stipend only. There are no additional benefits (such as provident fund, gratuity, health insurance, paid leave, or other employee benefits) unless separately agreed in writing by an authorized representative of Omninuera.

3. Duration
- Internship duration: 3 months.
- Start Date: [START_DATE].
- End Date: The internship will end three months after the Start Date. For example, if the Start Date is [START_DATE], the End Date will be [END_DATE] (calculated as [START_DATE] + 3 months).
- Any extension beyond the stated duration will require a separate written agreement.

4. Stipend and Payment
- Stipend: INR 10,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Thousand) per month.
- Payment Schedule: The stipend will be paid monthly in arrears, subject to deductions as required by applicable law and subject to satisfactory performance and attendance.
- Taxes: The stipend is subject to applicable taxes and statutory deductions as per Indian law. You are responsible for any personal income tax obligations unless Omninuera is required by law to withhold and remit taxes on your behalf.

5. Work Location and Jurisdiction
- Work Location: This is a completely remote internship. You will be based in Bengaluru, India.
- Jurisdiction: For the avoidance of doubt, any disputes arising out of or in connection with this internship shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in Bengaluru, India.

6. Working Hours and Commitment
- Expected weekly commitment: [WEEKLY_HOURS] hours per week (suggested range: 20–40 hours/week). Specific working days/times will be coordinated with your supervisor and may vary based on project needs.
- Flexibility: As a remote intern, you are expected to coordinate with your supervisor on deliverables, deadlines, and meetings. Regular attendance at scheduled meetings and timely completion of assignments is required.

7. Confidentiality and NDA
- Confidential Information: During the internship you may receive access to confidential, proprietary, and/or trade secret information of Omninuera. You agree to maintain the confidentiality of all such information and not to disclose it to any third party except as required to perform your duties for Omninuera or as authorized in writing.
- NDA: You may be required to sign Omninuera’s standard internship Non-Disclosure Agreement (NDA) as a condition of this internship. This offer is conditional upon your acceptance of the NDA, if requested.

8. Intellectual Property and Assignments
- Assignment of Inventions: You agree that all inventions, discoveries, developments, improvements, works of authorship, designs, ideas, processes, algorithms, data models, datasets, code, documentation, and other work product (collectively, "Work Product") created, developed, or reduced to practice by you, either alone or with others, during the internship and related to Omninuera's business or arising from tasks assigned by Omninuera, shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera.
- You shall promptly disclose such Work Product to Omninuera and hereby assign and agree to assign (and will cause your successors to assign) all rights, title, and interest in the Work Product to Omninuera. You shall assist Omninuera, at Omninuera’s expense, in securing patents, copyrights, or other protection for such Work Product and in perfecting Omninuera’s rights in the same.

9. Background Check and Pre-Conditions
- This offer is conditional upon satisfactory completion of background verification checks (education, employment history, criminal checks, or other checks as permitted by law). If any background check reveals information that Omninuera reasonably considers unsatisfactory, Omninuera may withdraw this offer or terminate the internship.
- Any other pre-employment or onboarding requirements (e.g., identity verification, submission of documents) must be completed prior to the Start Date as directed by Omninuera.

10. Termination and Notice
- Either party may terminate this internship by giving seven (7) days’ prior written notice to the other party.
- Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause (including, but not limited to, material breach of this letter, misconduct, violation of company policies, dishonesty, or breach of confidentiality).
- Upon termination, you must promptly return all Omninuera property, materials, and confidential information.

11. Compliance and Conduct
- You agree to comply with all company policies, codes of conduct, and cybersecurity and data protection policies applicable to interns. Omninuera may provide specific policies and training during the internship.
- You agree to follow instructions, maintain professional behavior, and perform the duties and responsibilities assigned by your supervisor.

12. Data Protection and Privacy
- Omninuera will process personal data about you for purposes related to recruitment, onboarding, payroll/stipend processing, performance management, and legal compliance. Such processing will be in accordance with applicable data protection and privacy laws.
- By accepting this offer, you consent to the collection and processing of your personal data for these purposes.

13. Internship Regulations and Labor Laws
- This internship is intended to comply with applicable Indian internship and labor regulations. Nothing in this letter is intended to violate applicable law. If any right or obligation under this arrangement is prescribed by mandatory statutory law, such statutory provisions shall apply.
- The internship does not entitle you to employee benefits except the stipend specified herein, unless agreed in writing.

14. Acceptance
- To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy of the signed letter to [HR_CONTACT_EMAIL] by [ACCEPTANCE_DEADLINE]. This offer is valid until [OFFER_EXPIRY_DATE], after which it may be withdrawn.
- This offer is conditional upon satisfactory background verification and completion of onboarding requirements.

15. Miscellaneous
- Amendments: Any amendment to this offer must be in writing and signed by an authorized representative of Omninuera.
- Severability: If any provision of this letter is held to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions will remain in full force and effect.

We are excited about the possibility of you joining Omninuera as an AI Intern and contributing to our projects. If you have any questions, please contact [HR_CONTACT_NAME], [HR_CONTACT_TITLE], at [HR_CONTACT_EMAIL] or [HR_CONTACT_PHONE].

